  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-3293">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 1. </span>
      Discuss with your counselor the importance of textiles. Explain the terms
      fiber, fabric, and textile. Give examples of textiles you use every day.
      <br /><i>Resource:</i>
      <a href="https://youtu.be/7-fLaXF6kOs?si=VNaU9JCXzi2FZEq7" target="_blank"
        >Textiles: What Are They? Where Do They Come From? (video)</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-3294">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 2. </span>
      Do the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-3294 mb-requirement-id-3295">
        (a) Get swatches of two natural fiber fabrics (100 percent cotton,
        linen, wool or silk; no blends). Get swatches of two synthetic fiber
        fabrics (nylon, polyester, acrylic, olefin, or spandex). Get a sample of
        one cellulosic fabric (rayon, acetate or lyocell).
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-3294 mb-requirement-id-3296">
        (b) Give the origin, major characteristics, and general content of each
        type of fiber obtained for 2(a). Explain the difference between a
        cellulosic manufactured fiber and a synthetic manufactured fiber.
        <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/cRLPUAPCfuo" target="_blank"
          >Natural vs Synthetic Fibers (Which to Choose and Why) (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-3294 mb-requirement-id-3297">
        (c) Describe the main steps in making raw fiber into yarn, and yarn into
        fabric. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/vFaNiTlHeCY" target="_blank"
          >From Cotton to Yarn (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/NIt9SGk55b4" target="_blank"
          >Weaving Process (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/yRXuKFy89Mg" target="_blank"
          >Knitting Process (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/5nUjGNDImIk" target="_blank"
          >Complete Process of Textile Manufacturing Fiber to Complete Garments
          (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-3294 mb-requirement-id-3298">
        (d) Assume you will soon buy a new garment or other textile item. Tell
        your counselor what fiber or blend of fibers you want the item to be,
        and give reasons for your choice.
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-3299">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 3. </span>
      Do TWO of the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-3299 mb-requirement-id-3300">
        (a) Visit a textile plant, textile products manufacturer or textile
        school or college. Report on what you saw and learned.
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-3299 mb-requirement-id-3301">
        (b) Weave a belt, headband, place mat or wall hanging. Use a simple loom
        that you have made yourself. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://www.theweavingloom.com/how-to-make-a-cardboard-loom/"
          target="_blank"
          >How to Make a Cardboard Loom (website)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-3299 mb-requirement-id-3302">
        (c) With a magnifying glass, examine a woven fabric, a nonwoven fabric,
        and a knitted fabric. Sketch what you see. Explain how the three
        constructions are different. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/2Q_04oCLZVs" target="_blank"
          >Woven vs. Knit vs. Non-Woven Fabrics | Textile Talk w/ A Thrifty
          Notion (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-3299 mb-requirement-id-3303">
        (d) Make a piece of felt. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/3IxCDkh-evs" target="_blank"
          >Wet Felting Tutorial for Beginners (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-3299 mb-requirement-id-3304">
        (e) Make two natural dyes and use them to dye a garment or a piece of
        fabric. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/jHpPuvibjZ8" target="_blank"
          >Natural Dyes From Plants and Vegetables | DIY Eco-Friendly Dyes |
          Homeschool with Everyday Food (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://www.youtube.com/shorts/J6Ib3Ehy_pw?feature=share"
          target="_blank"
          >Short Tie Dye Demo - No Narration (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://www.youtube.com/shorts/Oeth97r7VCw?feature=share"
          target="_blank"
          >Short Tie Dye Demo - With Narration (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-3299 mb-requirement-id-3305">
        (f) Waterproof a fabric. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/y83uXupu5tY" target="_blank"
          >A Simple DIY Way to Waterproof Anything (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/UlHfbltn6hI" target="_blank"
          >DIY Seam Seal (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-3299 mb-requirement-id-3306">
        (g) Demonstrate how to identify fibers, using microscope identification
        or the breaking test. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/BbeZvRi3eUI" target="_blank"
          >Identification of Basic Textile Fibers by Polarized Light Microscopy
          (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-3307">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 4. </span>
      Explain the meaning of 10 of the following terms: warp, harness, heddle,
      shed, aramid, spandex, sliver, yarn, spindle, distaff, loom, cellulose,
      sericulture, extrusion, carbon fibers, spinneret, staple, worsted,
      nonwoven, greige goods. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
      <a href="https://youtu.be/QNEB-fjMauc?si=zEm50ZTr7PgymZCE" target="_blank"
        >Loom and Weaving Terminology (video)</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-3308">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 5. </span>
      List the advantages and disadvantages of natural plant fibers, natural
      animal fibers, cellulosic manufactured fibers, and synthetic manufactured
      fibers. Identify and discuss at least four ecological concerns regarding
      the production and care of textiles. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
      <a href="https://youtu.be/lcq9tPI-W-c?si=7pT187LPR6ZCW2c0" target="_blank"
        >The Ultimate Fabric Guide - The Differences Between Natural vs
        Synthetic vs Semi-Synthetic Fibers (video)</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-3309">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 6. </span>
      Explain to your counselor, either verbally or in a written report, five
      career possibilities in the textile industry. Tell about two positions
      that interest you the most and the education, cost of training and
      specific duties those positions require. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
      <a href="https://youtu.be/uumtJp43Kfg?si=lOoILqksN5TWYQjK" target="_blank"
        >Careers in the Fashion &amp; Textiles Industry (video)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://youtu.be/Z-WValUr6z8" target="_blank"
        >Want to Work in the Textiles Industry? (video)</a
      ><br />
      <a
        href="https://www.youtube.com/shorts/rClr3NSF-CM?feature=share"
        target="_blank"
        >Textile Engineering Careers (video)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://youtu.be/Ify9Fo2IhB4" target="_blank"
        >Day in the Life of a Textile Engineer (video)</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
